Wild <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/usimix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Simix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/15/01 12:35:47 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.gigahosts.com/~c1003/aimicons/icons/fragglerock/wjfraggle7.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: trak - lessons learned</span><hr size=1> Ok, to those that don't know...the reason it takes awhile to actually charge trak once buffed (and the same reason the camp out plan may not work) is because you have to coordinate when to attack trak based on his position in the lair and the posistion of the juggs.  I was bind sighting trak the whole time for Jaharad who would pull the jugss based on when trak was in the back of the lair so he would not agro.  Especialy since this was our first time we had to make sure we attacked him at the most opportune time as possible.  Trak only moves every 20 minutes, so if he was sitting in the middle of the lair than we had to wait for him to run to the back.  As everyone can see by the second run, it pays to be a bit more patient and to attack him when we have the greatest advantage.<br>
<br>
Note : I would also like to reiterate the point a couple postes up about level making a huge deal in resists.  This is why many guilds only allow 54+ to come along on trak raids.<br>
